  "texts": [
    "For example, lines 37 -42 instruct the LLM to pick an appropriate FRED data series to download and specifies the format.",
    "Lines 92 -96 instruct the LLM to interpret the data to formulate a response in natural language.I hope that this simple example demystifies the \"magic\" of AI agents by showing that they are, at their core, programs that combine LLM reasoning with systematic access to external tools.",
    "It also highlights practical considerations like API calls (each question requires two LLM calls), latency (the multi-step process takes several seconds), and the importance of prompt engineering in getting reliable results from the reasoning engine.",
    "Perhaps most importantly, it provides a foundation that researchers can build upon, adding more data sources, more sophisticated analysis capabilities, or multi-agent coordination to tackle more complex research questions.The following example illustrates our simple agent in action:Chat 7 (econdata.py agent): How is the US labor market doing?=== THINK: LLM Call === Input:What FRED series code would help answer this question?",
    "Question: How is the US labor market doing?"
  ]
